{
  "stem": "8212.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "The place was pretty awful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "We had mice, so whenever we had some food like vegetables, we used to hang it up in bags on the walls so the mice couldn't eat it during the night.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "It was a very, very primitive existence.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And then they took my father away, the French.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "They put him in a French concentration camp called Saint-Cyprien.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "They took all the men, because they decided being that those men were coming from Vienna or Germany, even though being Jews, they were an enemy of the French state, because the war was with Germany.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And they just interned them, no matter what.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "They were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "They were running away anyway, but they put them in those terrible camps.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "So my father was put in Saint-Cyprien, which was near the Spanish border, a very primitive camp.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "After a few weeks, a few women decided to try and go there by train and see what's happening with their fathers and husbands.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "And I was by that time I think 12 years old or 13, and I decided-- we decided that I would go along and see-- my mother stayed with my sister-- and see what could be done.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "We arrived there, and being that I was a child, they let me go in.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "And I could see the conditions of this place.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "It was summer.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "People were just dressed very scantily in pajama pants or something.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "Lots of men were sick.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "They had malaria, cholera, because there were lots of germs there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "And they could only eat if they had something where the soup or something could be put in, like tin cans.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "If you had a tin can, you could have food, or you would have to lend the tin can to somebody else.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
